<TEXTAREA wrap=hard NAME="comment" ROWS="30" COLS="78" >政景＠鬼兜．E'ciさんは No.7026「PoS BRD2」で書きました。
>You say, 'I choose Clarisa.'
>Cilin Spellsinger says 'Take this book of songs and read it.  When you are 
>finished, hand it back to me and I will summon sweet Clarisa to test you. 
>
>Cilin Spellsinger から The Flute を受け取り、返します。
>
>Cilin Spellsinger says 'Farewell. 
>Clarisa Spiritsong says 'Rejoice and sing my friend. 
>
>Clarisa Spiritsong が現われ、Cilin Spellsinger が消えました。
>
>You say, 'Hail Clarisa Spiritsong'
>Clarisa Spiritsong says 'Hi there, Xxxxxx !  I give three sections of the 
>test of songs, Denise does the rest.  Do you wish to take the test of 
>pitch, voice, or tone? 
>
>You say, 'I choose pitch'
>Clarisa Spiritsong says 'The pitch that we sing and play has a great effect 
>on those who listen.  Keep this in mind, Xxxxxx , and you shall always be 
>welcome in taverns and inns.  Now, I need you to return to me a phosphoric 
>globe, a shimmering diamond, and a crude wooden flute. 
>
>You say, 'I choose voice'
>Clarisa Spiritsong says 'The sweet sounds rising forth from our throats are 
>what make us truly great.  Go forth and give voice to your songs, and 
>return to me a platinum disc, a music box, and a light woolen mantle.  If 
>you do this, I shall give you the mantle of the songweaver.  Good luck! 
>
>You say, 'I choose tone'
>Clarisa Spiritsong says 'Tone is important to all singers.  Prove to me 
>that you can keep your tone even and pure by bringng me an ochre tessera, a 
>songbird statuette, and a light woolen mask.  If you do this, I will give 
>you the mask of song.
</TEXTAREA><br>
